headline.main: DUP's Foster Resists Sinn Fein Calls to Go as Northern Ireland Talks Begin
headline.print_headline: DUP's Foster Resists Sinn Fein Calls to Go as Northern Ireland Talks Begin

lead_paragraph: Talks to save Northern Ireland's devolved government ran straight into an obstacle on Monday as Democratic Unionist Party (DUP) leader Arlene Foster resisted renewed demands by Irish nationalist party Sinn Fein not to return as first minister.
